6.2.3	
Circular sourcing

ISO/FDIS 59004:2024(en)
Implementing a circular economy involves:
—	 an understanding of the circularity in current operations, value creation models and related risks;
—	 identification of areas of opportunity to increase circularity (see Clause 6);
—	 leverage points and interactions along the value chain or value network and across different sectors and 
spheres of influence.

